This paper deals with machine learning models for question answering, which is a task commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the need for interpretability in these models, which is a topic of interest in the broader field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
